<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="7Dec1917"><font color="red">7 December 1917</font>, <cite>Pound Letters</cite> (Ezra Pound to LR): Mrs [H.G. Wells] has also sent on assurances of H.G.&apos;s admiration of Joyce. H.G.&apos;s review having been a valuable piece of imbecility &hellip; Joyce writes that the first division of his novel is at the typists. Enough for three numbers. So it looks as if we should be able to start him in March, O.K.</div>
